data.description: This impeccably designed Weston Dean home is the essence of a custom home with a thoughtful layout and state-of-the-art accents. After entering through the grand front door, step onto the eye-catching faux marble tile flooring. The open floor plan is an entertainer's dream with a meticulously crafted kitchen, covering over $32,000 in appliance enhancements. A chef's luxury, this kitchen is equipped with Wolf appliances. The Subzero panel-ready freezer blends with black cabinetry and contemporary hardware. The quartz counters gleam throughout the space with a stand-alone prep station with built-in storage and wine rack, in addition to the curved island. The dining and living spaces are highlighted by picturesque windows encompassing the home with natural light. The oversized primary suite features tray ceiling and dedicated space for a seating area. The remainder of the home boasts two secondary bedrooms, game room & office.
